; Supply-chain safeguard: only install dependency versions that have been
; published for more than 7 days. Freshly published (and potentially
; compromised) releases are excluded until they've had a week to be caught and
; pulled. This is a rolling window enforced on every install/update — semver
; ranges in package.json can't express version age, so it lives here.
; Docs: `npm help 9 min-release-age`.
min-release-age=7
